OL,6,FDuring more than an hour of
OL,7,Fquestioning by Stephen Leslie KC, Mr
OL,8,FPerks said he believed he encountered
OL,9,Fthe intruder on a lawned area behind
OL,10,Fthe conservatory, where the doors had
OL,11,Fbeen smashed, as his feet were "stood
OL,12,Fin something damp".
OL,14,F"My interpretation was that that was
OL,15,Fthe wet grass in the dark," he said.
OL,16,F"I have no recollection of walking
OL,17,Facross the broken glass."
