OL,6,FAgreeing with Mr Leslie that he had
OL,7,Fbeen stabbed outside, had turned and
OL,8,Fthen had a blank in his memory, Mr
OL,9,FPerks said: "I was confused about the
OL,10,Fevents going on.
OL,12,F"I was confused about the sequence of
OL,13,Fevents and why I was outside with a
OL,14,Ffigure who to me I thought was
OL,15,Fprobably my youngest son because he
OL,16,Fwas the same physique."
OL,18,FMr Leslie told jurors that Mr Perks'
OL,19,FDNA was found on a blue crowbar by a
OL,20,Fforensic scientist, along with an
OL,21,Funidentified finger mark.
